type: web_research
title: Cryptocurrency Temporal Patterns and Crash Prediction Techniques - Comprehensive Research
key_insights[19]: Monday effect in Bitcoin fading post-2020; Ethereum shows day-of-week effects post-COVID,Weekend trading share dropped from 24% (2018) to 17% (2023); liquidity worsening on weekends,"NY-London overlap (13:00-16:00 UTC) produces 31% higher volume; Asian session quietest",CME gaps fill rate 90-98% historically; gaps under $700 have 92% fill rate within 30 days,"Options expiry increases BTC volatility 5-8% weekly, 10-15% monthly, 18-25% quarterly",Max pain price magnetism observed in 6 days before settlement,"FOMC: BTC rallied after only 1/8 meetings in 2025; sell-the-news pattern dominant",DXY-BTC correlation ranges -0.3 to -0.8; strengthened during clear Fed policy direction,BTC-SP500 correlation increased from ~0 (pre-2020) to 0.50 avg (2025); peaked 0.90 mid-2025,"HMM with 4 states (bull, bear, calm + variant) outperform traditional models for crypto regime detection","EGARCH(1,1) often best GARCH variant for crypto; asymmetric models beat standard GARCH",DVOL (Deribit) serves as crypto VIX; positive correlation with price unlike traditional VIX,Funding rate spikes predict liquidation cascades within 12-24 hours,"October 2025 crash: $3.21B liquidated in 1 minute, $9.89B in 14 hours",LSTM+hybrid models achieve R²=0.99 for price prediction; crash prediction accuracy 64-79%,"Bitcoin halving cycle: 2024 peak at 534 days post-halving; diminishing returns each cycle",September consistently worst month for crypto; August-September underperformance robust,Tax-loss harvesting in Dec amplified by no wash-sale rule for crypto; January rebound pattern,Altcoin season when 75%+ of top 50 altcoins outperform BTC over 90 days; BTC.D key indicator
findings[8]: "Academic consensus: return seasonality weak/not robust; trading activity seasonality more robust","Institutional adoption changing all historical patterns - ETFs, derivatives growth key drivers","BTC acts as leveraged play on equities: SP500 +24% vs BTC +135% (2024); SP500 -19% vs BTC -65% (2022)","Asymmetric correlation: BTC ignores equity rallies but falls in tandem during selloffs",Global liquidity (M2) leads BTC by ~2 months; 41% of BTC movements tied to global liquidity,Combined Fear&Greed + RSI + MACD shows 73% win rate in backtests vs 50-55% for MACD alone,Yield curve de-inversion (re-steepening) more immediately dangerous than inversion itself,"Turn-of-month effect exists in Bitcoin; last trading days strongest, middle of month negative"
recommendations[5]: Use HMM for regime detection combined with GARCH for volatility modeling,"Monitor funding rates, OI, and liquidation patterns as leading crash indicators",DXY and global M2 liquidity as primary macro indicators for BTC direction,Combine sentiment (Fear&Greed) with technical (RSI/MACD) for multi-confirmation signals,Position defensively 18+ months post-halving based on historical cycle patterns
